description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Advanced Nurse Practioner General Surgery Band 8a&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Wirral University Teaching Hospital (WUTH) has an excellent opportunity for an enthusiastic, qualified Advanced Nurse Practitioner (ANP) to support the Upper GI and Colorectal Surgical Medical workforce. As part of the medical workforce the ANP will be working to support our 24/7 multidisciplinary approach to working.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The ANP must have achieved their MSc in Advanced Practice and be a competent Non-medical Prescriber (NMP) with the knowledge and skills to work at an 8a level. We are developing our team of highly skilled ANPs to promote high quality care, experience, outcomes and safe and effective discharge. We believe that ANPs significantly contribute to the patient journey and we would like a qualified ANP who is flexible and forward thinking to join our pre-existing friendly and supportive team of ANPs. Successful applicants will be supported in their development as Advanced Practitioners through high quality clinical supervision and access to relevant modules and negotiated study leave to support your development. Continuing Professional Development is an essential element to the ANP role.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The role of the Advanced Practitioner is dynamic and the post-holder will be proactive in pioneering and developing this role further in response to challenging healthcare needs and advances in practice.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will be expected to work alongside Doctors to ensure you can deliver excellent patient care at our Arrowe Park Hospital and Clatterbridge Hospital sites as part of our multidisciplinary Team working approach. The successful candidate will also have the opportunity to rotate between the specialities of Colorectal and Upper GI Surgery&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Advanced Nurse Practitioners with a dedication to best practice and a passion for improving health outcomes should apply to join our forward thinking multidisciplinary workforce. Our ANPs are highly valued and are well supported by the medical and senior nursing team and there will be opportunities for gaining skills and further development within the role.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The ideal candidate will have experience of working within a fast paced Acute Trust and want new challenges and to become part of an exciting and innovative multidisciplinary workforce.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Applicants will need to be NMC registered and be eligible to use their Independent Non-Medical prescribing qualification in practice in order to meet the criteria for this Qualified Advanced Practitioner post. Above all, we need Advanced Practitioners who are motivated and enthusiastic with a “can do” attitude who will deliver quality services with compassion.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Consideration will be given to applicants who wish to work full or part time.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Shortlisted candidates will be expected to bring a portfolio and one of your referees should be a Consultant who can comment on your clinical competence.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;.For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Name: LISA GIBB&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Job title ADVANCED NURSE PRACTITIONER COLORECTAL SURGERY&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Email address lisagibb@nhs.net&lt;/p&gt;
